When a galvanic cell is drained it has no more capacity to produce voltage. At the same time, when a galvanic cell is drained all ionic concentrations have changed from the initial molarities used to build up the cell. Overall, we have that 
\begin{equation}
\boxed{\Delta \mathcal{E}=0}
 \hspace{1cm} \textcolor{blue}{\text{drained cell}}
    \label{\chapterlabel:equation6}
\end{equation}  
